          "scid": "thig3.1:1.0.3",
          "en": "1. Another Sāmā"
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig3.1:1.0.4",
          "en": "“Full five-and-twenty years since I came forth! But in my troubled heart in no way yet Could I discern the calm of victory."
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig3.1:1.0.5",
          "en": "The peace of mind, the governance of thoughts Long sought, I found not; and with anguish thrilled I dwelt in memory on the Conqueror’s word."
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig3.1:1.0.6",
          "en": "To free my path from all that breedeth Ill I strove with passionate ardour, and I won! Craving is dead, and the Lord’s will is done. To-day is now the seventh day since first Was withered up within that ancient Thirst.”"
        }
      ],
